        {
          "type": "frame",
          "id": "KMj0R",
          "name": "Section-Status",
          "context": "<!--\n## Section-Status\n\n**Type:** component\n**Component:** StatusDot, StatusChip\n\n### Purpose\nThe atomic status indicators reused by RepoRow, BranchRow, sidebar leaves, and toasts.\n\n### Design notes\n- Dot 8px. Chip 22 tall, dot + label + Geist Mono 11.\n- Synced dot fill = $tag-success-ink. Failed dot fill = $tag-danger-ink.\n- Syncing dot = hollow ring, 1px stroke $color-text-secondary. Stale dot = hollow ring, 1px stroke $color-text-tertiary. Both intentionally stay neutral grey — these aren't tag categories, they're 'no signal' / 'in progress' states.\n- StatusChip-synced surface tinted $tag-success-wash; chip-failed surface tinted $tag-danger-wash; chip text always $color-text-primary (the danger/info inks fail contrast as label text). Syncing/stale chips stay white surface + grey border.\n-->",
