        {
          "type": "frame",
          "id": "Nsv7y",
          "name": "LoginScreen-wrap",
          "layout": "vertical",
          "gap": 12,
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "ER6nr",
              "name": "loginLabel",
              "fill": "#9b9295",
              "content": "01 / Login",
              "lineHeight": 1,
              "fontFamily": "Geist",
              "fontSize": 12,
              "fontWeight": "500"
            },
            {
              "type": "frame",
              "id": "Y9lv7W",
              "name": "LoginScreen-default-final",
              "context": "<!--\n## LoginScreen-default-final\n\n**Type:** layout\n**Variant:** default\n**Component:** LoginScreen\n\n### Purpose\nUnified entry point at /login. Two OAuth options (GitHub primary for connectors, Google for viewers). Signing with either lands the user on /.\n\n### Design notes\n- Surface: page bg #F6F8F9, card surface #ffffff, radius 16, 1px #E1E4E5.\n- Typography: Geist 24/500 headline, Geist 14 #6d6467 subhead, Geist 12 #9b9295 legal.\n- AuthButton variants live in Dashboard-Components-Kit (AuthButton-github-default-final, AuthButton-google-default-final).\n- GitHub button is dark (#121111 fill / white text). Google button is white surface with #E1E4E5 border. Both 44px tall, radius 14.\n- Google sign-in is enough to view shared instances. Connecting a repo on /connect prompts to link a GitHub identity if the user came in via Google (per dashboard-build-plan.md auth flow split).\n\n### For AI agents\n- Demonstrates the only screen reachable while signed-out.\n- After auth, route to / which is Dashboard-empty-final (zero repos) or Dashboard-populated-final.\n- Do not add password / email fields. OAuth only.\n-->",
              "width": 1440,
              "height": 900,
              "fill": "#ffffff",
              "cornerRadius": 16,
              "stroke": {
                "align": "inside",
                "thickness": 1,
                "fill": "#E1E4E5"
              },
              "layout": "vertical",
              "justifyContent": "center",
              "alignItems": "center",
              "children": [
                {
                  "type": "frame",
                  "id": "V1osn",
                  "name": "Login-Card",
                  "context": "<!--\n## Login-Card\n\n**Type:** layout\n**Variant:** default (signed-out entry)\n**Component:** LoginCard\n\n### Purpose\nThe /login surface — first thing a signed-out user sees. Two-button auth (GitHub + Google) inside a self-contained card. GitHub-first since the product reads from GitHub repos; Google is the lighter sign-in alternative for users who do not yet have a linked GitHub (per build plan, those users hit a blocking link-GitHub modal on /connect later).\n\n### Design notes\n- Card is 480 wide, radius 40, gradient bg ($color-bg-primary at 0.5 → $color-bg-secondary at 1.0, rotation 180°), 1px $color-border-primary stroke. Friendlier and more object-like than the dashboard panel (which uses radius 16 + flat fill).\n- Vertical rhythm: gap 32, padding 24. Stack: Login-Brand → Header (title + subtitle) → List & Label (AuthList + legal microcopy).\n- Title 24/normal #121111 centered, subtitle 14/normal #6d6467 centered.\n\n### For AI agents\n- Sister surface to the connect/dashboard wraps but signed-out — note that this is the actual surface, not a wrap frame, so ship as-is.\n- The AuthList inside reuses the same gray-surface + stacked-rows primitive as RepoList (PyuN0, aHZOW), connS2List, and Recent Repos. Decision deferred to the codebase agent on whether to share a single List/RowList container or keep AuthList as a sibling — proportions differ slightly (radius 20 + padding 4 here vs radius 18 + padding 2 on RepoList).\n- Two known mismatches inside this card to fix when porting:\n  1. AuthButton frame names are swapped relative to their content (see yA9R9 / Nqeid notes).\n  2. Google button uses the lucide 'globe' icon, not a real Google G mark — swap before shipping (Google brand guidelines are strict).\n-->",
                  "width": 480,
                  "fill": {
                    "type": "gradient",
                    "gradientType": "linear",
                    "enabled": true,
                    "rotation": 180,
                    "size": {
                      "height": 1
                    },
                    "colors": [
                      {
                        "color": "$color-bg-primary",
                        "position": 0.5
                      },
                      {
                        "color": "$color-bg-secondary",
                        "position": 1
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  "cornerRadius": 40,
                  "stroke": {
                    "align": "inside",
                    "thickness": 1,
                    "fill": "$color-border-primary"
                  },
                  "layout": "vertical",
                  "gap": 32,
                  "padding": 24,
                  "alignItems": "center",
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "type": "frame",
                      "id": "C1xC9g",
                      "name": "Login-Brand",
                      "context": "small horizontal lockup: 28px dark mark + 'Component Canvas' wordmark in Geist 14/500. only place on the canvas where the brand mark renders directly, so this pair is the canonical reference for a future Brand component.",
                      "gap": 10,
                      "alignItems": "center",
                      "children": [
                        {
                          "type": "frame",
                          "id": "HuKjq",
                          "name": "Login-Mark",
                          "context": "brand mark: 28px dark square (radius 8, fill #121111), centered lucide 'layers' icon at 16px white. swap icon and/or fill if the brand evolves — keep the 28px / radius 8 ratio so the lockup proportions stay intact.",
                          "width": 28,
                          "height": 28,
                          "fill": "#121111ff",
                          "cornerRadius": 8,
                          "justifyContent": "center",
                          "alignItems": "center",
                          "children": [
                            {
                              "type": "icon_font",
                              "id": "GEnRJ",
