                    {
                      "type": "frame",
                      "id": "Wf6BD",
                      "name": "List & Label",
                      "context": "auth buttons + legal microcopy below them. the legal text below a CTA cluster mirrors the layout pattern used by ConnectRepo-Footer-final ('Organization repos require admin install...'). consider a shared 'Disclaimer' text style once it shows up in a third place.",
                      "width": "fill_container",
                      "layout": "vertical",
                      "gap": 12,
                      "children": [
                        {
                          "type": "frame",
                          "id": "q6pOgd",
                          "name": "AuthList",
                          "context": "<!--\n## AuthList\n\n**Type:** section\n**Variant:** stacked auth buttons\n**Component:** AuthList / RowList (auth variant)\n\n### Purpose\nHolds the two AuthButton children stacked vertically. GitHub first (primary path), Google second (alt path).\n\n### Design notes\n- Surface primitive: #f0f3f4 fill, radius 20, 4px padding, 1px stroke, gap 4. Slightly chunkier than the RepoList primitive (radius 18, padding 2, gap 2) — likely because the buttons are 44 tall + radius 16 and need a touch more breathing room around the inner pills.\n\n### For AI agents\n- Same family of primitive as RepoList (PyuN0, aHZOW), connS2List, and Recent Repos: a gray-surfaced container that holds white-pill children. Strong candidate for the same shared RowList primitive proposed on those wraps, with proportions parameterized.\n- Note: this node previously carried the RepoList context comment by mistake — it has been corrected. If you see the old text resurface, it is likely an editor-state artifact rather than intent.\n-->",
                          "clip": true,
                          "width": "fill_container",
                          "fill": "#f0f3f4",
                          "cornerRadius": 20,
                          "stroke": {
                            "align": "inside",
                            "thickness": 1
                          },
                          "layout": "vertical",
                          "gap": 4,
                          "padding": 4,
                          "children": [
                            {
                              "type": "frame",
                              "id": "yA9R9",
                              "name": "AuthButton-google-default-final",
                              "context": "<!--\n## AuthButton — GitHub (default)\n\n**Type:** state\n**Variant:** default (resting)\n**Component:** AuthButton\n\n### Design notes\n- Pill, 44 tall, radius 16, white fill, 16/20 padding, gap 8 between icon and label.\n- Icon: lucide 'github' at 16px #6d6467. Label: 'Continue with GitHub' Geist 14/500 #6d6467.\n\n### For AI agents\n- Naming bug: this frame is named 'AuthButton-google-default-final' but renders GitHub. Sibling Nqeid has the inverse mismatch. Fix one (preferably rename the frames to match content) when this lands in code.\n- Hover, pressed, and loading states should live in the kit alongside this default once they exist. Hover likely darkens the fill slightly and bumps icon + label to #121111.\n-->",
                              "width": "fill_container",
                              "height": 44,
                              "fill": "#ffffff",
                              "cornerRadius": 16,
                              "gap": 8,
                              "padding": [
                                16,
                                20
                              ],
                              "justifyContent": "center",
                              "alignItems": "center",
                              "children": [
                                {
                                  "type": "icon_font",
