                      "type": "frame",
                      "id": "i1YX9",
                      "name": "EmptyState-Card",
                      "context": "<!--\n## EmptyState-Card\n\n**Type:** layout\n**Variant:** default (no repos connected, signed-in)\n**Component:** EmptyStateCard\n\n### Purpose\nCentered card on / for a signed-in user who has not connected any repos yet. Single primary CTA: Connect a repo. The end-of-flow companion to Login-Card — same visual vessel, different copy and a different next step.\n\n### Design notes\n- Card geometry mirrors Login-Card exactly: 480 wide, radius 40, gradient bg ($color-bg-primary at 0.5 → $color-bg-secondary at 1.0, rotation 180°), 1px $color-border-primary stroke, padding 24, gap 32. The intentional visual rhyme says these are siblings: the empty-canvas surfaces that frame a single primary action.\n- Internal stack: EmptyState-Icon → Header (title 24/normal #121111 + subtitle 14/normal #6d6467) → List & Label (CTA pill + legal microcopy).\n- CTA is full-width inside the card (44 tall, radius 16, dark fill) — heavier than the dashboard 36-tall connect button because this surface has no other content competing for attention.\n\n### For AI agents\n- Keep this card and Login-Card visually locked. If one moves (radius, gradient, padding), the other should move with it. They are the only two surfaces using this gradient + radius 40 vessel.\n- Older simpler variants live in Section-EmptyState (LAiBC EmptyState-default-final, nAAVw EmptyState-with-sample-cta-final). Those were the previous canonical empty state and are kept around as a smaller card style — i1YX9 is the current one.\n- The 'with sample components' secondary link from EmptyState-with-sample-cta-final has not been carried over here. If product wants the sample-CTA path back, port the secondary link below the primary CTA inside fIzgW.\n-->",
