                    {
                      "type": "frame",
                      "id": "KNRCz",
                      "name": "Recent Repos",
                      "context": "<!--\n## Recent Repos\n\n**Type:** section\n**Variant:** highlighted card grid\n**Component:** RecentRepos / CardGrid\n\n### Purpose\nMost accessed repos shortcut row above the all-repos list. One card is rendered in highlighted state (dark gradient) to pull attention to the most recent / most active repo.\n\n### Design notes\n- Surface primitive: #f0f3f4 fill, radius 18, 2px padding, 1px stroke. Same primitive as RepoList and ConnectRepo-Step3.\n- Header bar Most accessed repos uses the Text Holder pattern (Geist 14 #9b9295). Same pattern as Assign to workspace on ConnectRepo-Step3.\n- Inner Repos frame holds 3 horizontal Repo Card cells, each 160 tall with radius 16. One uses the dark gradient highlight, two are plain white.\n\n### For AI agents\n- This section and ConnectRepo-Step3 are the same visual primitive at different scales and palettes:\n  - Recent Repos = 3 repo cards, dark gradient = most accessed highlight, click = navigate to repo.\n  - ConnectRepo-Step3 = 2 workspace cards, blue gradient = selected highlight, click = radio select.\n- Suggested consolidation: one CardGrid container + one base Card component with variants for content (workspace vs repo) and state (default vs highlighted/selected). The codebase agent decides whether the prop surface justifies a single component or two cousins sharing a primitive.\n- Equivalent on Dashboard-populated-wrap is s4QqfU (same structure, same children, same highlighted card).\n-->",
                      "width": "fill_container",
                      "fill": "#f0f3f4ff",
                      "cornerRadius": 18,
                      "stroke": {
                        "align": "inside",
                        "thickness": 1
                      },
