                    {
                      "type": "frame",
                      "id": "aHZOW",
                      "name": "RepoList",
                      "context": "<!--\n## RepoList\n\n**Type:** section\n**Variant:** stacked rows (with one row expanded inline)\n**Component:** RepoList / RowList\n\n### Purpose\nThe all-repos panel. Vertical list of RepoRow children at root depth, plus BranchRow children indented under the one expanded repo.\n\n### Design notes\n- Surface primitive: #f0f3f4 fill, radius 18, 2px padding, 1px stroke. Same primitive as Recent Repos and ConnectRepo-Step3.\n- Children are individually-styled white pills (radius 16) sitting in the gray container — separator-free, gap 2.\n\n### For AI agents\n- Strong candidate for splitting into two primitives:\n  - RowList container — owns the gray surface, padding, gap, optional clip.\n  - Row base — the white pill, radius 16, with content slots.\n  Then RepoRow / BranchRow / OtherBranchesExpander / ConnectRepoRow all become Row variants. The codebase agent should evaluate whether row content variation (chevron + org/repo + chip vs pin + branch + sha + meta vs radio + repo) is wide enough to justify the abstraction or whether siblings are clearer.\n- Note that connS2List on ConnectRepo-wrap is the same surface primitive with selectable rows. If the consolidation lands, it should adopt the same RowList wrapper.\n- Equivalent on Dashboard-populated-wrap is PyuN0 (same primitive, all-default rows + one hover + state showcase).\n-->",
                      "clip": true,
                      "width": "fill_container",
                      "fill": "#f0f3f4",
                      "cornerRadius": 18,
                      "stroke": {
                        "align": "inside",
                        "thickness": 1
