              "type": "frame",
              "id": "y6krPp",
              "name": "ConnectRepo-default-final",
              "context": "<!--\n## ConnectRepo-default-final\n\n**Type:** layout\n**Variant:** default (one repo selected)\n**Component:** ConnectRepo\n\n### Purpose\nThe /connect flow. Pick a GitHub installation, pick a repository, choose which workspace owns it, and submit (build plan lines 132, 141, 188–190).\n\n### Design notes\n- Surface: page bg #F6F8F9, form panel #ffffff with radius 16 + 1px #E1E4E5.\n- Two-column form, single panel. Sections: GitHub installation → Repository → Workspace assignment → Footer.\n- 'Step labels' use Geist 11/500 #9b9295 uppercase tracking, mirroring the STATE label pattern from variant-toggle-final on the canvas.\n- Repo rows use Geist Mono 14 for org/repo. Selected row has #F6F8F9 fill + filled radio.\n- Workspace radio cards mirror RepoRow workspace chips: Personal (dot + label), Team Acme (mono initial avatar + label).\n- New repos default to Personal per build plan line 132 — this layout shows a user changing the destination to Acme.\n\n### For AI agents\n- Sibling state variants live in component kit (ConnectRepoForm-{state}-final).\n- Cancel returns to /. Connect repo returns to / and adds the new RepoRow at the top of the list with status 'Syncing… initial build'.\n- Google-only users hit a blocking link-GitHub modal here (not shown in this layout).\n-->",
              "clip": true,
              "width": 1440,
              "height": 900,
              "fill": "#ffffff",
              "cornerRadius": 16,
