                      "context": "<!--\n## ConnectRepo-Step2\n\n**Type:** section\n**Variant:** repo picker (single-select)\n**Component:** ConnectRepoStep / RepoPicker\n\n### Purpose\nStep 2 of /connect. User picks one repo from the GitHub installation. Single-select via radio. Already-connected repos are listed but disabled.\n\n### Design notes\n- Inner connS2List uses the same #f0f3f4 surface + radius 18 + 2px padding + 1px stroke primitive as RepoList and Recent Repos.\n- Selected row swaps to #F6F8F9 fill + filled radio. Default rows show empty radio + already-connected meta.\n\n### For AI agents\n- Same row-list pattern as RepoList on the dashboards, just with selection affordances instead of meta + status. Worth considering whether RepoList and connS2List share a base list-of-rows container component.\n- Step 2 to Step 3 is a wizard handoff; selection state lives on the parent ConnectRepo container.\n-->",
