                    {
                      "type": "frame",
                      "id": "R1zlTn",
                      "name": "ConnectRepo-Step3",
                      "context": "<!--\n## ConnectRepo-Step3\n\n**Type:** section\n**Variant:** workspace assignment (radio cards)\n**Component:** WorkspacePicker\n\n### Purpose\nStep 3 of /connect. User assigns the new repo to either Personal or one of their teams. Default per build plan line 132 is Personal; this layout shows a user overriding to Acme.\n\n### Design notes\n- Outer container reuses the same surface primitive as Recent Repos and RepoList: #f0f3f4 fill, radius 18, 2px padding, 1px stroke.\n- Two WorkspaceCard children stacked horizontally inside the Workspaces frame — one default white, one selected with a soft blue gradient highlight.\n- Assign to workspace label sits inside a Text Holder bar, same pattern as the Most accessed repos header above the Recent Repos cards on the dashboards.\n\n### For AI agents\n- Visually near-identical in structure to Recent Repos on Dashboard-populated-wrap (s4QqfU) and Dashboard-expanded-wrap (KNRCz): header bar + horizontal grid of medium cards in a #f0f3f4 surface.\n- Use cases differ:\n  - ConnectRepo-Step3 = single-select radio for workspace assignment.\n  - Recent Repos = clickable shortcuts to recently-accessed repos.\n- Strong candidate for one unified Card component (or shared Card primitive) with variants:\n  - workspace-default / workspace-selected (this section)\n  - repo-recent / repo-recent-highlighted (Recent Repos)\n  And one shared CardGrid container that both sections instantiate.\n- Do not enforce the consolidation here — the codebase agent decides based on actual prop overlap, accessibility roles (radio vs link), and how click handlers diverge.\n-->",
                      "width": "fill_container",
                      "fill": "#f0f3f4ff",
                      "cornerRadius": 18,
                      "stroke": {
