    {
      "type": "note",
      "id": "l2I23",
      "x": -1984,
      "y": 3870,
      "name": "Dashboard-Gap-Analysis-final",
      "width": 1440,
      "height": 520,
      "content": "<!--\n## Gap Analysis — dashboard-build-plan.md vs. delivered design\n\nCross-referenced against build plan lines 121–276. Documents what's covered, what's still missing, and where each gap should live in the design before code begins.\n\n### Already designed in `pzqsk` (Dashboard-Layouts-Container)\n- /login (LoginScreen-default-final)\n- / dashboard — empty, populated, expanded (with branches + WorkspacePopover open)\n- /connect (ConnectRepo-default-final, repo-selected variant)\n- /[workspace]/[repo]/[branch] — AppShell-with-breadcrumb-final (the only structural change to AppShell per build plan line 176)\n\n### Designed in `sZN5H` (Components Kit) — handled by parallel agent\n- AuthButton, TopBar, RepoRow, WorkspaceChip, WorkspacePopover, BranchRow, StatusDot/Chip, OtherBranchesExpander, EmptyState, ConnectRepoForm, InstanceBreadcrumb, SidebarLeaf, SidebarFolder, IconButton, Toast.\n\n### Still missing (recommended next pass)\n1. **Initial-sync waiting screen** (build plan line 99). Full-canvas overlay shown after a brand-new repo connection while the first build runs (1–5 min). Should mount inside the AppShell with progress meta (clone → detect entry → bundle N of M).\n2. **Build-failed full panel** (line 261). When the customer's repo doesn't compile. Sidebar leaves grayed; canvas shows the inline build error log.\n3. **Component-init error inline** (lines 258, 261). Per-leaf failure: 'couldn't initialize this component' + error text + Re-sync button.\n4. **Server-component disabled leaf** (line 253). Sidebar leaf with lock icon + 'Server component — not supported' tooltip.\n5. **Stale-viewer banner** (line 233, Step 7). Top-of-canvas banner shown via Supabase Realtime when a new sync arrives mid-session.\n6. **Share-link dialog** (line 232, Step 7). Token-scoped URLs. Default scope: signed-in-anyone.\n7. **Invite-members modal + Manage-members screen** (line 229). Email invitations + role picker, beyond the hover popover.\n8. **Workspace-conversion dialog** (line 229). Personal → team upgrade.\n9. **Link-GitHub modal** (lines 113, 312). Surfaces only when a Google-only viewer clicks 'Connect a repo'.\n10. **Not-supported-stack screen** (line 276). Hard refusal at /connect when the repo's stack falls outside the bounded support matrix (RSC-only, JS-only, non-Tailwind, etc.).\n11. **What's-new feed** (line 237, Step 8). Recent syncs + changed components, surfaced in the dashboard or AppShell.\n12. **Workspace-switcher popover** (top bar). Clicking the workspace pill should open a list of joined workspaces, the personal one, and 'Create team workspace'.\n13. **Connect-flow auto-pin defaults** (line 311). Visual: branch glob defaults (`main`, `feat/*`, `release/*`) shown with editable chips at the end of the connect flow.\n14. **Sample-repo CTA** (line 309). 'Try with sample components' secondary action on the empty state — kit covers the variant; no full layout needed.\n\n### Tension to flag\n- Build-plan line 153 explicitly says 'No card-based grids, no big tiles, no recently-opened carousels.' The sibling layout `Dashboard-populated-v2-with-featured-cards-final` deliberately departs from this rule to explore a 'most accessed / recently active' hero section per the user request. Keep `Dashboard-populated-final` as the canonical no-cards version; `v2` is an exploration, not a replacement.\n-->"
    },
    {
      "type": "note",
      "id": "UJrU3",
      "x": 1100,
      "y": 3816,
      "name": "Design-Token-Reference-final",
      "width": 1440,
      "height": 340,
      "content": "<!--\n## Design Token Reference — bound to apps/web/app/global.css\n\nThe `.pen` document exposes design-token variables that mirror the live tokens in `apps/web/app/global.css`. Use `$variable-name` in node properties to bind future work.\n\n### Colors (semantic)\n- `$color-bg-primary` #FFFFFF · `$color-bg-secondary` #F6F6F9 · `$color-bg-tertiary` #EFF0F5\n- `$color-bg-elevated` #FFFFFF · `$color-bg-hover` #F6F6F9 · `$color-bg-hover-elevated` #F6F6F9\n- `$color-border-primary` #E6E7EF · `$color-border-secondary` #DFE0E7\n- `$color-text-primary` #121111 · `$color-text-secondary` #6D6467 · `$color-text-tertiary` #9B9295\n- `$color-canvas-dot` rgba(0,0,0,0.07) — dotted infinite-canvas marker\n\n### Tag colors (UI indicators only — not brand/marketing)\nEach tag = (wash, ink) pair. wash = soft chip/pill background. ink = strong accent for icon, dot, border, or solid bg. For label text, prefer `$color-text-primary` on wash (warning & info inks are too light to use as label text on white — accent only).\n\n- `$tag-success-wash` #ECFDF5 / `$tag-success-ink` #1D8D44\n  Positive/healthy: synced, completed, live, active, online, stable.\n- `$tag-warning-wash` #FEFAF1 / `$tag-warning-ink` #F49E0A\n  Needs attention but not broken: pending, expiring, throttled, beta, in-progress.\n- `$tag-info-wash` #DAEAFE / `$tag-info-ink` #0EA6E7\n  Neutral information / labels (not a state): draft, scheduled, in review, syncing, note.\n- `$tag-danger-wash` #FEF1F1 / `$tag-danger-ink` #E15072\n  Errors and destructive: failed, blocked, removed, critical, deprecated. Doubles as the destructive color.\n- `$tag-highlight-wash` #F8FFBB / `$tag-highlight-ink` #3C4209\n  High-energy spotlight, no severity: NEW, FEATURED, TRENDING, recently-added markers. Eye-catching wash, dark olive ink.\n- `$tag-archive-wash` #FFE1BB / `$tag-archive-ink` #7E5422\n  Historic / low-priority: archived, paused, sandbox, draft envs, legacy. Warm faded combo — 'still here, not active'.\n\nUsage rules:\n1) Reach for these only when a status/category needs visual coding — a neutral chip uses --color-bg-tertiary + --color-text-primary.\n2) Solid variant: ink as fill + white text.\n3) Subtle variant: wash as fill + ink as icon/dot/border + --color-text-primary for the label text.\n4) Don't mix tag families inside one component or one row of chips.\n\n### Gradients (decorative — string vars; pen color tokens can't hold gradient stops)\n- `$gradient-dawn` linear-gradient(180deg, #AFCBE3 0%, #D3DBEE 30%, #E5C4CB 85%, #C0C4E1 100%)\n- `$gradient-dusk` linear-gradient(180deg, #040405 0%, #22273C 17%, #6B8D9C 48%, #F5F6F1 100%)\n- `$gradient-daylight` linear-gradient(180deg, #FCE576 5%, #F5F7EE 57%, #F7F8F5 100%)\nUse for hero / splash / time-of-day moments only. Recreate as a gradient fill matching the CSS in the variable.\n\n### Spacing (px)\n`$spacing-0` 0, `$spacing-1` 2, `$spacing-2` 4, `$spacing-2-5` 6, `$spacing-3` 8, `$spacing-3-5` 10, `$spacing-4` 12, `$spacing-5` 16, `$spacing-6` 20, `$spacing-7` 24, `$spacing-8` 28, `$spacing-9` 32, `$spacing-10` 40, `$spacing-11` 48, `$spacing-12` 64, `$spacing-13` 80, `$spacing-14` 120, `$spacing-15` 160, `$spacing-16` 200\n\n### Radius (px)\n`$radius-0` 2, `$radius-1` 4, `$radius-1-5` 6, `$radius-2` 8, `$radius-2-5` 10, `$radius-3` 12, `$radius-4` 16, `$radius-5` 20, `$radius-6` 24, `$radius-full` 9999\n\n### Type sizes (px)\n`$type-1-size` 8, `$type-2-size` 10, `$type-3-size` 12, `$type-4-size` 14, `$type-5-size` 16, `$type-6-size` 18, `$type-7-size` 20, `$type-8-size` 24, `$type-9-size` 28, `$type-10-size` 32, `$type-11-size` 36, `$type-12-size` 40, `$type-13-size` 48\n(line-heights and weights live in CSS via .type-N classes; in pencil set `lineHeight` per the global.css table — 1.5 for type-1..5, 1.25 for type-6..8, 1.15 for type-9..11, 1.0 for type-12..13.)\n\n### Font\n`$font-sans` Geist (single family across the entire app per global.css; Geist Mono is used for technical strings like org/repo, SHA, ISO timestamps).\n\n### Sub-token exceptions\n- StatusDot/StatusChip stroke thickness 1.5 — intentional (1 reads thin, 2 reads heavy). Keep until the token system grows.\n-->"
    },
