    {
      "type": "frame",
      "id": "qQaV5",
      "x": 9866,
      "y": 6000,
      "name": "Dashboard-populated-v2-wrap",
      "layout": "vertical",
      "gap": 12,
      "children": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "id": "Pqzak",
          "name": "v2Label",
          "fill": "#9b9295",
          "content": "03b / Dashboard — populated v2 (with featured cards section)",
          "lineHeight": 1,
          "fontFamily": "Geist",
          "fontSize": 12,
          "fontWeight": "500"
        },
        {
          "type": "frame",
          "id": "vyo5t",
          "name": "Dashboard-populated-v2-with-featured-cards-final",
          "context": "<!--\n## Dashboard-populated-v2-with-featured-cards-final\n\n**Type:** layout\n**Variant:** populated + featured-cards iteration\n**Component:** Dashboard\n\n### Purpose\nExploratory iteration of the populated dashboard with a 'Recently active' card section above the canonical 'All repos' list. Intended to evaluate a hero-card affordance for high-frequency repos without abandoning the dense list pattern below.\n\n### Tension with build plan\nBuild-plan line 153 explicitly says 'No card-based grids, no big tiles, no recently-opened carousels.' This layout deliberately departs from that rule per user direction to explore highlight cards. Treat this as an A/B candidate, not the canonical surface — `Dashboard-populated-final` (sibling) remains the no-cards reference.\n\n### Design notes\n- Section heading 'Recently active' (Geist 16/500) + Geist 12 #9b9295 muted meta (`Last 7 days`).\n- Cards: white surface, radius 16, 1px #dfe0e7, no heavy preview imagery (per user direction). Card density mirrors Reference17 cards (Reference16/17 are pinned on the canvas as moodboard).\n- Each card carries: org/repo (Geist Mono 14), branch + last-sync meta, StatusChip top-right, component-count footer meta, primary 'Open' pill action footer-right.\n- Below cards: existing 'All repos' page header + RepoList (copied verbatim from `Dashboard-populated-final` so this iteration matches the canonical content).\n\n### For AI agents\n- Card variants explored further in `FeaturedRepoCard-iterations-final` (sibling block in `pzqsk`): Iteration A (this layout), Iteration B (compact), Iteration C (metrics-led), Iteration D (activity-led).\n- Treat the all-repos list panel as the source of truth for repo data; the cards are derived selections (most active, most recently synced, etc.).\n- Do not delete `Dashboard-populated-final`. The two coexist deliberately until the user picks one.\n-->",
          "clip": true,
          "width": 1440,
          "height": 1280,
          "fill": "#f6f6f9ff",
          "cornerRadius": 16,
          "stroke": {
            "align": "inside",
            "thickness": 1,
            "fill": "#dfe0e7"
          },
          "layout": "vertical",
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "frame",
              "id": "Co9pM",
              "layoutPosition": "absolute",
              "x": -9999,
              "y": -9999,
              "name": "v2Tb",
              "context": "<!--\n## DashboardTopBar-final\n\n**Type:** component\n**Variant:** default\n**Component:** DashboardTopBar\n\n### Purpose\nPersistent top bar across /, /connect, and /[workspace]/[repo]/[branch]. Provides workspace switching, global search, primary 'Connect new repo' action, and the user avatar.\n\n### Design notes\n- 64px tall, 1440 wide. White surface with #E1E4E5 bottom hairline only.\n- Workspace switcher mirrors Sidebar-Header (8zJLA): dark mono initial avatar, two-line meta, chevrons-up-down trigger.\n- Search input mirrors Sidebar-Search-Bar (XlkGy): 32px tall, 1px #E1E4E5 border, lucide search icon, mono placeholder for fuzzy repo lookups.\n- Primary action (#121111 fill, white label, radius 14) is `+ Connect new repo` per build plan line 132.\n- Avatar 32px, dark fill, mono initial.\n- Reusable so all dashboard layouts share the same bar.\n\n### For AI agents\n- Override `WorkspaceSwitcher-name` text via descendants to switch contexts.\n- Override `Connect-Label` for variants like 'Connect first repo' on the empty state.\n- The bar itself never changes structurally between layouts — only inner copy.\n-->",
              "width": 1440,
              "height": 64,
              "fill": "#ffffffff",
              "stroke": {
                "align": "inside",
                "thickness": {
                  "bottom": 1
                },
                "fill": "#E1E4E5"
              },
              "padding": [
                0,
                16
              ],
              "justifyContent": "space_between",
              "alignItems": "center",
              "children": [
                {
                  "type": "frame",
                  "id": "F5bqO",
                  "name": "TopBar-Left",
                  "gap": 12,
                  "alignItems": "center",
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "type": "frame",
                      "id": "HAWZy",
                      "name": "TopBar-Brand",
                      "width": 28,
                      "height": 28,
                      "fill": "#121111ff",
                      "cornerRadius": 8,
                      "justifyContent": "center",
                      "alignItems": "center",
                      "children": [
                        {
                          "type": "icon_font",
                          "id": "R1gRj0",
                          "name": "tbBrandIcon",
                          "width": 16,
                          "height": 16,
                          "iconFontName": "layers",
                          "iconFontFamily": "lucide",
                          "fill": "#ffffff"
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "frame",
                      "id": "Q1W2x",
                      "name": "WorkspaceSwitcher-final",
                      "context": "<!-- ## WorkspaceSwitcher-final\n**Type:** component\n**Variant:** default (closed)\n**Component:** WorkspaceSwitcher\n### Design notes\n- White pill, radius 14, 1px #E1E4E5, padding 6. 24×24 mono initial avatar + 2-line meta (workspace name + role) + chevrons-up-down trigger.\n- Lives in DashboardTopBar-final and at top of Sidebar (mirrors `8zJLA` in `bMuHk`).\n### For AI agents\n- Clicking opens WorkspaceSwitcher-popover (NOT YET DESIGNED — see gap-analysis note).\n- Override `WorkspaceSwitcher-Name` text via descendants when used as a ref.\n-->",
                      "fill": "#ffffffff",
                      "cornerRadius": 12,
                      "stroke": {
                        "align": "inside",
                        "thickness": 1,
                        "fill": "#E1E4E5"
                      },
                      "gap": 8,
                      "padding": 6,
                      "alignItems": "center",
                      "children": [
