          "fontWeight": "500"
        },
        {
          "type": "frame",
          "id": "bazX6",
          "name": "FeaturedRepoCard-iterations-final",
          "context": "<!--\n## FeaturedRepoCard-iterations-final\n\n**Type:** layout\n**Variant:** exploration block\n**Component:** FeaturedRepoCard\n\n### Purpose\nSide-by-side card iterations to evaluate before locking on a single FeaturedRepoCard style. Each column is one iteration with the same example repo (`acme/design-system`) so the user can compare information density and tone.\n\n### Iterations\n- **A — Reference (canonical):** rendered live in `Dashboard-populated-v2-with-featured-cards-final`. Mirrors the Reference17 supply-card structure (title + meta header, status chip, divider, footer with count + Open action).\n- **B — Compact row:** single horizontal line per card; status chip + open icon. Best for showing many at once.\n- **C — Metrics-led:** big number in the center (component count or branches). Best when discoverability of scale matters.\n- **D — Activity-led:** last commit + author surfaced. Best for change-aware browsing.\n\n### For AI agents\n- Pick whichever iteration the user lands on; promote the chosen variant into the kit (`FeaturedRepoCard-default-final`, etc.).\n- All cards must remain monochrome — colored backgrounds violate the dense, type-driven visual language (build plan line 154).\n-->",
          "width": 1440,
          "fill": "#eff0f5ff",
          "cornerRadius": 16,
          "layout": "vertical",
          "gap": 24,
          "padding": 48,
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "frame",
              "id": "R6zIRy",
              "name": "Iterations-Row",
              "context": "<!-- ## Iterations-Row\n**Type:** layout container\n**Variant:** card iterations exploration\n**Component:** FeaturedRepoCard-iterations\n### Design notes\n- 4 columns: Iteration A (reference) | B (compact) | C (metrics-led) | D (activity-led). Gap 24, fill_container.\n-->",
