    {
      "type": "frame",
      "id": "UAxrX",
      "x": 2433,
      "y": 5478,
      "name": "Dashboard-Components-Kit-v2-Container",
      "context": "<!--\n## Dashboard-Components-Kit-v2-Container\n\n**Type:** kit container\n**Variant:** v2 — refreshed design language\n**Component:** Dashboard component kit (next gen)\n\n### Purpose\nNext-gen of Dashboard-Components-Kit-Container (sZN5H). Mirrors the structure of the old kit but every section is rebuilt against the design language established in Dashboard-Layouts-Container (pzqsk).\n\n### What changed vs the old kit\n- Gradient HeroCard vessel (radius 40 + gradient + soft 1px stroke) replaces the old flat empty-state card.\n- Gray-surface list primitive (#f0f3f4 / radius 18 / 2px padding / 1px stroke) holds white-pill rows uniformly across RepoRow, BranchRow, ConnectRepoForm.\n- Card grids with one highlighted card (dark or blue gradient) appear under recent-repos and workspace pickers.\n- Stronger nesting: list-of-rows containers always sit inside the section, never directly on the kit surface.\n- Section labels live in a small Text Holder bar above grouped content (mirrors Dashboard-Layouts greeting + connect headers).\n\n### What's deliberately not here\n- AuthButton and WorkspacePopover stay exclusive to the old kit per task scope.\n\n### For AI agents\n- Each section follows the same skeleton: heading 16/500, description 14/normal #6d6467, then a Display frame on a #f0f3f4 surface that demonstrates the variants.\n- The Display surface itself uses radius 18 + 1px stroke to echo the list primitive in the new layouts.\n- Cross-reference with Dashboard-Layouts-Container (pzqsk) when a component appears in a screen there — keep proportions, gradients, and radii in lockstep with the layout surfaces.\n-->",
      "width": 1072,
      "fill": "#F0F3F4",
      "cornerRadius": 24,
      "layout": "vertical",
      "gap": 48,
      "padding": 48,
      "children": [
