        {
          "type": "frame",
          "id": "OzlhI",
          "name": "Section-Status-v2",
          "context": "<!--\n## Section-Status-v2\n\n**Type:** component\n**Component:** StatusDot, StatusChip\n\n### Purpose\nAtomic indicators reused by RepoRow, BranchRow, sidebar leaves, toasts, and the stale-viewer banner.\n\n### Design notes (v2)\n- Dot 8px, ellipse. Synced fill $tag-success-ink, failed fill $tag-danger-ink, info fill $tag-info-ink. Syncing/stale stay neutral grey rings (no fill) — they're 'no signal' states, not tag categories.\n- Chip 24 tall, radius full, padding [4,10], gap 6, dot + Geist Mono 11/500 label. Synced/failed/info chips use the matching wash surface. Syncing/stale chips stay white + 1px $color-border-secondary.\n- Captions on this kit use Geist 11/500 #9b9295 uppercase letter-spacing 1 — same SectionLabel pattern that recurs across the v2 kit.\n\n### For AI agents\n- The semantic hand-off: dots carry status on RepoRow / BranchRow, chips replace dots when there's room for a label (Toast, expanded RepoRow header).\n- Keep dots/chips visually locked across kit sections — RepoRow-syncing-final's dot must be the same dot rendered here.\n-->",
