        {
          "type": "frame",
          "id": "Bji9C",
          "name": "Section-RepoRow-v2",
          "context": "<!--\n## Section-RepoRow-v2\n\n**Type:** component\n**Component:** RepoRow\n\n### Purpose\nThe scrollable list row on the dashboard `/`. One row per connected repo, expandable to reveal pinned BranchRows.\n\n### Design notes (v2)\n- Row pill: 56 tall, radius 16, white fill, padding [16,20], layout horizontal, gap 16, justifyContent space_between.\n- Left cluster: chevron-right icon (12, $color-text-tertiary) + Geist Mono 14 #121111 org/repo.\n- Right cluster: revealed action icons on hover (Open / Re-sync / Pin) + Geist Mono 12 #6d6467 meta + 8px status dot + WorkspaceChip.\n- Expanded variant: fill #f6f8f9, chevron-down (rotated). The BranchRow children below share the same #f6f8f9 fill so the expanded group reads as one block visually.\n- Hover variant: subtle 1px #E1E4E5 inside ring + slightly tinted #f6f8f9 fill — strong enough to anchor the hover cluster without yelling.\n\n### For AI agents\n- Status dot semantics match Section-Status: synced ($tag-success-ink), syncing (ring $color-text-secondary), failed ($tag-danger-ink), stale (ring $color-text-tertiary).\n- The row pill never carries semantic color itself — the dot, chip, and meta line do all the talking. This keeps the list calm.\n- Inside the dashboard, RepoRows live inside a gray ListContainer (radius 18 / padding 2 / 1px stroke / gap 2). The kit display reuses that primitive so the visual context is preserved.\n-->",
          "width": "fill_container",
          "fill": "#ffffff",
          "cornerRadius": 16,
          "stroke": {
            "align": "inside",
            "thickness": 1,
            "fill": "#E1E4E5"
