        {
          "type": "frame",
          "id": "PR3eE",
          "name": "Section-OtherBranchesExpander-v2",
          "context": "<!--\n## Section-OtherBranchesExpander-v2\n\n**Type:** component\n**Component:** OtherBranchesExpander\n\n### Purpose\nLazy-loads remaining (unpinned) branches from GitHub when clicked. Lives directly under the last pinned BranchRow inside an expanded RepoRow.\n\n### Design notes (v2)\n- 40 tall, indented 32 (padding [10,20,10,48]). Same #f6f8f9 fill as BranchRow so it visually attaches to the expanded group.\n- Label is Geist 13 #6d6467 + Geist Mono 12 #9b9295 count badge. Trailing chevron-down rotates 180° when expanded.\n- Loading state replaces the chevron with a 12px spinner (rotated 'loader-2').\n\n### For AI agents\n- Place this row last inside the BranchRow stack — it is the affordance to fetch the rest.\n- Once expanded, the parent RepoRow renders the lazy-loaded branches as additional BranchRow children below this expander.\n-->",
          "width": "fill_container",
          "fill": "#ffffff",
