    {
      "type": "frame",
      "id": "bmFW0",
      "layoutPosition": "absolute",
      "x": 5176,
      "y": 7956,
      "name": "DashboardNav-final",
      "context": "<!--\n## DashboardNav-final\n\n**Type:** component\n**Variant:** default\n**Component:** DashboardNav\n\n### Purpose\nPersistent top nav across /, /connect, and /[workspace]/[repo]/[branch]. Hosts the (future) brand logo, the global search input (cmd+K), the primary 'Connect Repo' CTA, the user avatar, and the theme toggle. Author's preferred top bar — replaces the earlier DashboardTopBar-final.\n\n### Design notes\n- 1440 wide × 60 tall (12 padding × 2 + 36 controls). White (#ffffff) surface, padding [12, 40].\n- `clip: true` on the root so the layout-balancer slot does not bleed pixels.\n- Layout is `space-between`: Nav-LogoSlot ↔ Nav-Search ↔ Nav-Right. Nav-LogoSlot is sized to mirror Nav-Right so the search visually centers.\n- Search bar 480 wide, white pill radius 12, lucide search glyph + Geist 14 placeholder + ⌘K kbd hint pill.\n- Connect button is dark (#171719 fill, white Ronzino 16 label), radius 12, padding [16,20], height 36.\n- Avatar + ThemeToggle are 36×36 circles with a dark→cool-blue→cream gradient placeholder fill.\n\n### For AI agents\n- When codifying the connect button, replace `Nav-Connect-Button` with the dark variant of the project's PrimaryButton system rather than reproducing this frame. Override `Nav-Connect-Label` text via descendants if a specific layout needs different copy.\n- `Nav-Avatar` should bind to the shadcn Avatar primitive; the gradient fill is the fallback when no GitHub/Google profile image is available. Clicking should open a user-controls popover (logout, settings) — popover is not yet designed.\n- `Nav-ThemeToggle` should bind to the existing lightmode/darkmode toggle so the dashboard shell respects the same theme as the runtime app (already wired there). Replace the gradient placeholder fill with the actual sun/moon glyph when that asset exists.\n- `Nav-LogoSlot` is currently empty — drop the brand mark inside when one exists. Keep its width matched to Nav-Right so space-between continues to center Nav-Search. 'component-canvas' is a working product name only — do not type-set it as a wordmark.\n- Override `Nav-Search-Placeholder` text via descendants for context-specific placeholders (e.g. focused state).\n-->",
      "reusable": true,
      "clip": true,
      "width": 1440,
      "fill": "#ffffffff",
      "stroke": {
        "align": "inside",
        "thickness": 1
      },
      "gap": 64,
      "padding": [
        12,
        40
      ],
      "justifyContent": "space_between",
      "alignItems": "center",
      "children": [
        {
          "type": "rectangle",
          "id": "sF7Fe",
          "name": "Nav-LogoSlot",
          "context": "<!-- ## Nav-LogoSlot\n**Type:** layout balancer / future logo slot\n**Component:** DashboardNav\n### Design notes\n- Empty for now. Width 238 mirrors Nav-Right (Connect button + avatar + theme toggle cluster) so the parent's `space-between` layout visually centers Nav-Search.\n### For AI agents\n- When the brand logo exists, drop it inside this slot. Keep this frame's width matched to Nav-Right so space-between continues to center Nav-Search.\n- 'component-canvas' is the working product name only — do not type-set it as a wordmark.\n-->",
          "fill": "#00000000",
          "width": 238,
          "height": 36,
          "stroke": {
            "thickness": 0
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "frame",
          "id": "uXeQw",
